snippet.textDisplay: Between December 2003 and October 2005, more than 100 human cases of avian influenza and more than 60 deaths, caused by the H5N1 strain, have been detected in Cambodia, China, Indonesia, Thailand and Viet Nam. H5N1 avian influenza is a public health concern because of its potential to spark a pandemic.
